					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13092766#post-4525849</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13092766/scp-5850#post-4525849</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 01 Mar 2020 18:35:36 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>JakdragonX</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>5588260</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I tried to base the dialogue off of things I would say, or how people around me usually talk. I'll have to make some adjustments it seems, but hopefully the dialogue as it stands isnt <strong>terribly</strong> unbelievable. I didnt mean for it go overboard.</p> <p>I'm terrible with dialogue, but I think what you're referring to are the first and last video transcripts? I've messed around with the third one a bit to make it sound more realistic, but theres really not alot of talking in either of them to be able to change alot. I wanted to keep them minimal (atleast the first one) because of the &quot;hook&quot; I wanted for the narrative, and to express the mood between characters like Williams and Rains.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13092766#post-4525842</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13092766/scp-5850#post-4525842</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Sun, 01 Mar 2020 18:22:27 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>ThadeusOfNazereth</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>6073727</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I upvoted - the concept of a multiverse of afterlives is really compelling, and I think this article does a really good job of setting up future tales, articles, and canons that explore that idea. I'll echo what the above poster said about the dialogue, though - it didn't feel very realistic (especially the &quot;I can't hear my haters&quot; exchange).</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
					<item>
